docs.lead_paragraph: Our dispatches from Honolulu are to the 27th of August. The Committee appointed to consider the petition for the removal of the Ministers, JUDD and ARMSTRONG, reported on the 15th of August adversely to the petition. The popular feeling, particularly among the foreigners, who are almost unanimous, appear to run high against the Missionaries.

docs.lead_paragraph: JOHN DUFFY, of New-York, has been appointed Consul to Galway, Ireland, and ALOIS D. GALL, of Indiana, Consul to Antwerp. docs.lead_paragraph: We showed in our last article on this subject, that there is an excess of officers in the Navy as now constituted, and presented some of the evils resulting from such excess. The inquiry how this excess can be disposed of, is an important one to the country and to the service.

docs.lead_paragraph: AN INVITATION TO NEW-ORLEANS.--The weather has again become cool and delightful, and we take occasion to reassure our absent citizens, and also strangers, that there is not the least danger in coming to the city.

docs.lead_paragraph: It is quite fashionable in England, Just now, to speak of Quarantine regulations as relics of a barbarous age,--useless inconveniences,--often intolerable nuisances.

headline.main: ANOTHER CABINET LETTER.; The Charge of Disunion--The Administration and Internal Improvements--Hon. Jefferson Davis on Senator Toombs. From the Griffin (Ga.) Jeffersonian.

docs.lead_paragraph: SIR: Your letter 0f the 2Oth ult., arrived here during my absence, and ill-health has combined with constant occupation, thus far, to delay my reply.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Story a Thousand Times Told, yet Always New. "Oh! will you not let me rest here one night? I have not where to lay my head." If you will go with me up town, dear leader, I will point you to an elegant mansion, in which once dwelt a family reared in all the luxury which wealth can purchase and indulgence lavish.
